Third-party components
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Every dependency — in source distributions and in the statically-linked binary
distributions alike (the PyPI wheels and the npm Node-API addons) — is under a
permissive licence (MIT, Apache-2.0, BSD, ISC, Zlib, Unicode, or similar). The
allowed set is enforced in CI by `cargo deny` (see `deny.toml`), which fails the
build on any dependency outside it.

Note: the Python parser (`rustpython-parser`) is built with its `num-bigint`
feature rather than the default `malachite-bigint`, so the LGPL-3.0-only
`malachite` bignum library is NOT part of this project's dependency tree. See the
comment on `rustpython-parser` in the workspace `Cargo.toml`.
